{
  "text": "PopMedNet 2 is a scalable and extensible opensource platform to simplify the implementation and operation of distributed health data querying networks. This platform was developed by HMORN (Health Maintenance Organisation Research Network), a consortium of 19 U.S. regional healthcare delivery organisations. Through a set of web-based services and tools, PopMedNet enables the creation and use of distributed data networks. It supports both menus driven queries and distributed analyses using complex, single-use or multi-use programs and returns aggregated counts of eligible study cohorts [CITATION_1] .",
